# Code Conventions

## Components

- Functional components + hooks ONLY (no class components)
- Props interface: `{ComponentName}Props`
- Named exports only (no default exports)
- Colocated tests: `ComponentName.test.tsx`

## TypeScript

- Strict mode — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for simple types
- Import types: `import type { X } from "..."`

## Files

- kebab-case for files: `element-utils.ts`
- PascalCase for components: `LayerUI.tsx`

## How to verify

1. Confirm new React components are function components and use named exports only
2. Confirm component props types follow the `{ComponentName}Props` naming pattern
3. Confirm touched TypeScript code does not introduce `any` or `@ts-ignore`
4. Confirm type-only imports use `import type` and simple aliases prefer `type` over `interface`
5. Confirm tests stay colocated with components and file names follow the documented casing rules
